HEADWORD: Pseudotetramera
<hw>Pseu`do*te*tram"e*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Pseudo-</er>, and <er>Tetramerous</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of beetles having the fifth tarsal
joint minute and obscure, so that there appear to be but four
joints.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Pseu`do*te*tram"er*al</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
